# GoSteady firmware Kconfig — project-local symbols.
#
# Imports the standard Zephyr Kconfig tree first, then adds GoSteady-
# specific switches. Set values in prj.conf (always-on bench config)
# or in an overlay like prj_field.conf (deployment).

mainmenu "GoSteady firmware configuration"

source "Kconfig.zephyr"

menu "GoSteady"

config GOSTEADY_FIELD_MODE
	bool "Build for deployment (field) mode"
	default n
	help
	  When enabled, the firmware is built for unattended deployment
	  operation per the M10.5 spec:

	    - SW0 button handler is disabled (no manual session start).
	    - uart1 dump channel is not started (and with it, the BLE NUS
	      tunnel that piggybacks on uart1 from the bridge — `START`
	      from capture.html no longer routes to a session-start path).
	    - LED heartbeat tick (purple blink) is silenced. Recording-
	      time green LED is also silenced. Only the M12.1e pre-
	      activation blue LED remains in deployment.
	    - Heartbeat log line on uart0 is silenced.
	    - Auto-start uses FIELD_PREWALK (subject_id="deployed",
	      course_id="field", etc.) instead of the bench placeholders;
	      patient attribution is cloud-side per portal contract.

	  Pure motion-driven autonomous capture: ADXL367 wake-on-motion
	  → BMI270 confirmation → session → M9-motion-gate auto-stop.

	  Default off so bench builds keep all existing tooling. Build
	  the deployment image with:

	    west build -b thingy91x/nrf9151/ns -- -DEXTRA_CONF_FILE=prj_field.conf

config GOSTEADY_CLOUD_ENABLE
	bool "Enable AWS IoT MQTT/TLS cloud bring-up"
	default n
	help
	  When enabled, src/cloud.c is compiled and main() spawns the
	  one-shot heartbeat publisher worker on boot. The publisher
	  waits for cellular registration + network time, opens an MQTT/
	  TLS connection to AWS IoT Core (cert at sec_tag 201, provisioned
	  via tools/flash_cert.py), publishes one heartbeat to
	  gs/{client_id}/heartbeat, and exits.

	  Default off so bench data-collection runs (M8 captures via
	  capture.html / pull_sessions.py) are undisturbed by cellular
	  activity at boot. The ~78 KB of aws_iot + mqtt_helper + mbedTLS
	  + TLS sockets that come along with this Kconfig are also paid
	  for only in builds that opt in.

	  Three build configurations:

	    west build                                              # bench, no cloud — default M8 data-collection workflow
	    west build -- -DEXTRA_CONF_FILE=prj_cloud.conf          # bench + cloud — for M12.1c.1+ on-device cloud testing
	    west build -- -DEXTRA_CONF_FILE=prj_field.conf          # deployment — FIELD_MODE + cloud

	  prj_field.conf includes the cloud block inline so deployment
	  builds need only the single overlay; prj_cloud.conf is the
	  same block factored out for bench cloud-testing without
	  pulling in FIELD_MODE.

endmenu
